<section class="sec-cream" id="designer">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="founder-grid">
      <div class="founder-text reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">{{ section.settings.eyebrow }}</span>
        <p class="founder-quote">
          {{ section.settings.quote }}
        </p>

        <div class="founder-body prose">
          {% comment %}
            <p>
              In my practice, I hear the same story every week. A patient comes in. They hate their smile. They have
              stopped being in photos with their kids. They want it fixed, but the clinical reality is brutal: traditional
              porcelain veneers mean hours in my chair, permanently drilling down healthy enamel, and a bill between ten
              and twenty thousand dollars.
            </p>

            <p>For most hardworking people, that is not an option.</p>

            <p>
              So they go online and buy a cheap plastic snap-on for a couple hundred dollars. A few weeks later, they are
              sitting in my chair again, showing me what arrived. It is always the same. The appliance is stamped from a
              single mold. The gingival margin, the gumline, is a straight, thick plastic ridge. The teeth look like
              identical white piano keys. They put it in, realize everyone can immediately tell it is fake, and throw it
              in a drawer.
            </p>

            <p>
              They paid good money to feel worse than when they started. And the companies selling these things keep
              selling them anyway, because the customer is too embarrassed to complain publicly.
            </p>

            <p>
              I got tired of seeing it. I know exactly what makes a tooth look real. It is not magic. It is proportion,
              translucency, and how the edge meets the gum. I knew those clinical standards could be engineered into a
              removable appliance if someone actually did the work. So I did.
            </p>

            <p>
              Every Revive case is produced against the 7-Point Smile Design Protocol I built. If a case does not pass my
              standard, it does not ship.
            </p>
          {% endcomment %}
          {{ section.settings.story }}
        </div>

        <p class="founder-shield">
          {{ section.settings.shield }}
        </p>

        <div class="founder-body prose">
          {{ section.settings.bottom_story }}
        </div>

        <div class="sig-block">
          {% if section.settings.signature_image != blank %}
            <img
              src="{{ section.settings.signature_image | image_url: width: 250 }}"
              alt="{{ section.settings.founder_name }}"
              class="sig-img"
              width="120"
              height="120"
            >
          {% else %}
            <img
              src="{{ 'founder-image.jfif' | asset_url }}"
              alt="{{ section.settings.founder_name }}"
              class="sig-img"
              width="120"
              height="120"
            >
          {% endif %}
          <div class="sig-name">{{ section.settings.founder_name }}</div>

          <div class="sig-sub">{{ section.settings.founder_designation }}</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="founder-media reveal" data-delay="100">
        <div class="founder-video">
          <span class="vlabel">[ Video · Dr. Turley ]</span>
          <div class="sc-play" id="turleyOverlay">
            <span class="pbtn">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
                <path d="M6 4l14 8-14 8z"></path>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>

        {% comment %}
          <div class="founder-creds">
            <div class="cred">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.9"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"></circle>
                <path d="M12 7v5l3 2"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>12+ Years Experience</span>
            </div>

            <div class="cred">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.9"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <path
                  d="M12 4c3 0 5 1.6 5 4.5 0 1.6-.5 3-.9 5.2-.4 2.2-.6 5.3-2.1 5.3-1.3 0-1.2-3-2-3s-.7 3-2 3c-1.5 0-1.7-3.1-2.1-5.3C7.5 11.5 7 10.1 7 8.5 7 5.6 9 4 12 4Z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Cosmetic Dentist</span>
            </div>

            <div class="cred">
              <svg
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.9"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
              >
                <path d="M12 3l8 3v6c0 5-3.5 8-8 9-4.5-1-8-4-8-9V6z"></path>
                <path d="M8.5 12.5l2.5 2.5L16 10"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Creator of the 7-Point Protocol</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        {% endcomment %}
        <div class="founder-creds">
          {% for block in section.blocks %}
            {% if block.type == 'credential' %}
              <div class="cred" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
                {% if block.settings.icon_svg != blank %}
                  {{ block.settings.icon_svg }}
                {% endif %}

                <span>
                  {{ block.settings.text }}
                </span>
              </div>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Post Quiz Founder Story",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "What I kept watching."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "quote",
      "label": "Quote",
      "default": "I have sat across from patients who cover their mouths when they laugh. It is the hardest thing to watch as a dentist."
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "story",
      "label": "Main Story",
      "default": "<p>In my practice, I hear the same story every week. A patient comes in. They hate their smile. They have stopped being in photos with their kids. They want it fixed, but the clinical reality is brutal: traditional porcelain veneers mean hours in my chair, permanently drilling down healthy enamel, and a bill between ten and twenty thousand dollars.</p><p>For most hardworking people, that is not an option.</p><p>So they go online and buy a cheap plastic snap-on for a couple hundred dollars. A few weeks later, they are sitting in my chair again, showing me what arrived. It is always the same. The appliance is stamped from a single mold. The gingival margin, the gumline, is a straight, thick plastic ridge. The teeth look like identical white piano keys. They put it in, realize everyone can immediately tell it is fake, and throw it in a drawer.</p><p>They paid good money to feel worse than when they started. And the companies selling these things keep selling them anyway, because the customer is too embarrassed to complain publicly.</p><p>I got tired of seeing it. I know exactly what makes a tooth look real. It is not magic. It is proportion, translucency, and how the edge meets the gum. I knew those clinical standards could be engineered into a removable appliance if someone actually did the work. So I did.</p><p>Every Revive case is produced against the 7-Point Smile Design Protocol I built. If a case does not pass my standard, it does not ship.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "shield",
      "label": "Shield Text",
      "default": "Let me be clear about one thing. I am a cosmetic dentist, but I am not your dentist, and Revive is not dental treatment. I designed a product."
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "bottom_story",
      "label": "Bottom Story",
      "default": "<p>I designed the standard behind it too, so a more natural-looking appliance could be made for people who had almost given up on their smile.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "founder_name",
      "label": "Founder Name",
      "default": "Dr. Brandon Turley, DDS"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "founder_designation",
      "label": "Founder Designation",
      "default": "Doctor of Dental Surgery · Founder, Revive Teeth"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "video_label",
      "label": "Video Label",
      "default": "[ Video · Dr. Turley ]"
    }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "credential",
      "name": "Credential",
      "settings": [
        {
          "type": "textarea",
          "id": "icon_svg",
          "label": "SVG"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "text",
          "label": "Text"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Post Quiz Founder Story",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "credential",
          "settings": {
            "text": "12+ Years Experience"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "credential",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Cosmetic Dentist"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "credential",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Creator of the 7-Point Protocol"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
